From: Octopus Orchestrator upstream PR draft wave (M0-16)
Subject: [PATCH] gateway: advertise features.octo from hello-ok handshake

Wire buildFeaturesOcto (already implemented in src/octo/wire/features.ts)
into the Gateway hello-ok handshake so clients can feature-detect
Octopus Orchestrator support via features.octo?.enabled === true.

The octo key is always emitted, even when octo.enabled: false — in that
case buildFeaturesOcto returns the canonical disabled descriptor
(empty adapters, baseline capabilities). Clients gate on the enabled
boolean, not on key presence, matching the contract in
docs/octopus-orchestrator/HLD.md §Feature advertisement via
hello-ok.features.octo.

No new schema, no new transport, no new config keys. enabled and
adapters are sourced from the loaded octo config (loadOctoConfig,
M0-11) and passed through verbatim — the handshake layer performs no
filtering or policy of its own.

No behavior change for deployments with octo.enabled: false (default
through Milestone 1): clients simply see enabled: false and hide
their Octopus UI.

Draft authored against upstream commit 9ece252.

